Diagnosis.
Male (
Fig. 29
). Body dark brown without metallic luster. Both oval velvety black orbital spots and velvety black parafacial spots between eye and antenna present (
Fig. 30–31
). Frons with pair of posterior orbital setae. Antennal scape and pedicel yellowish brown, antennal flagellum black except basally yellow (
Fig. 30
). Mesonotum brown with two or three darker brown longitudinal stripes (
Fig. 31
). One pair of apical scutellar setae present (
Fig. 31
). Hind femur with distinct ventral spines. Hind tibia yellow with brown rings in middle and apical portion (
Fig. 32
). Wing hyaline and immaculate, both anterior and posterior crossveins darker. Posterior crossvein straight (
Fig. 33
). Female similar to male in external characters except terminalia.

Male terminalia: Sternum 5 divided into two transversely subquadrate sclerites (
Fig. 34
). Cercus elongated, rod-like (
Fig. 35
). Surstylus short, semicircular and fused medially (
Fig. 35–36
). Hypandrium symmetrical, tapering to apex (
Figs 37–38
). Aedeagus and apodemes as shown in 
Figs. 39–40
.

Distribution. China ( Hebei , Beijing , Shandong , Henan , Shaanxi , Zhejiang , Sichuan , Guizhou , Yunnan , Hubei , Guangxi , Fujian ); South and North Korea , Japan , Philippines (
Rozkošný et al ., 2010
).
